We first compute the average owner's equity using the beginning and ending balances from the balance sheet.

Step 1: Identify Owner’s Equity values.
• Beginning Owner’s Equity (2023-12-31): 13,000,000.00 
• Ending Owner’s Equity (2024-01-29): 11,824,937.81

Step 2: Calculate the average Owner’s Equity.
  Average Owner’s Equity = (Beginning Owner’s Equity + Ending Owner’s Equity) / 2
  = (13,000,000.00 + 11,824,937.81) / 2
  = 24,824,937.81 / 2
  ≈ 12,412,468.91

Step 3: Identify the Net Profit from the income statement.
  Net Profit = -1,175,062.19

Step 4: Calculate ROE using:
  ROE = (Net Profit) / (Average Owner’s Equity)
  = -1,175,062.19 / 12,412,468.91
  ≈ -0.09465, or about -9.47%

Thus, the Return on Equity (ROE) is approximately -9.47%.

  }
